  <number>34.</number>
  <discussion>Species 13 (4 in the flora):</discussion>
  <discussion>Microbryum is similar to Syntrichia in its broad leaves, single stereid band, and
        red reaction of the lamina to KOH, but differs in the short stems, distinctive reduction
        series involving the sporophyte, round to semicircular costal stereid band (reniform in
        Syntrichia), peristomes (when present) of 16 irregular, often rudimentary, truncate
        peristome teeth that are large in comparison with the size of the capsule, and operculum
        (when present) low-conic. Adaxial costal pads of cells are occasionally present (in M.
        vlassovii). Distinguishing features include variation in ornamentation and size of the
        spores, and collections of these monoicous taxa usually include sporophytes.</discussion>
